args:
Lathna states that she was the cause of the
strange incident. However, Cleo suspects the
truth to be more complex, and so the pair begin
an investigation. After learning of a suspicious
woman, they pursue her to a cave downriver.
Now that we've met up with everyone,\nwe can finally take a breather.
While they're holding off the assault,\nwe need to find the cause of this.
We both know that I'm the one who made\nthe lanterns turn into zombies.
That's why I'm just going to go back to the\nHalidom. Before more lanterns come up\nthe river.
But Lathna, you were so looking forward\nto the festival.
It's...okay. I should be alone. I won't make\ntrouble for you and everyone else that way.
You may say as much, but you couldn't\nlook more broken up about it.
You don't like being alone, do you?\nI can tell.
I've heard a little bit about your\ncircumstances. That spell you cast was\nnot done so through your own volition.
Furthermore, you have no connection to\nthose lanterns coming upriver. You had\nonly just arrived in town.
Even if it WAS your spell which turned the\nlanterns into zombies, I believe the cause\nof the phenomenon lies elsewhere.
Maybe... But I still can't totally believe\nthat.
Then let us seek out the truth and resolve\nthe matter together. I'll give it my all.
But... I wonder if we CAN resolve it.
Ye of little faith. Let's start by\ngathering some information.
I'd like to hear from the people who\nfloated lanterns on the river, but...
Everyone is terrified. We're not going to be\nable to get them to talk if they're like that.
Indeed. Good thing I've got a special\nsecret plan for just such a situation.\nLeave it to me.
Man, this is a lifesaver! They really got\nthis shelter up during the night, huh?\nHope it's as zombie-proof as it looks.
I hear the people from the Halidom are\npatrolling the area. We can finally breathe.
Yeah. And they laid out all this food for\nus, too.
I THOUGHT I smelled something\ngood! Let's go get our grub on.
Amazing. They were so afraid before, but\nnow they're fine. Is this your secret plan?
It is. A roof overhead and a hot meal\ngo a long way toward relieving anxiety!

With everyone out of harm's way, we
should have much less trouble gathering
information. Two birds, one stone. Now,
let's get to asking some questions.
You're telling me the food's all gone?\nNo way!
What?! I made a veritable mountain of it!\nIt looks as though there are more people\nwho had to seek refuge than I thought.
I don't want them going hungry, but this\nwill keep me too busy to go around asking\nquestions...
Um, maybe... I could go and ask around.
What? I thought you didn't like talking to\npeople. Are you sure you'd be okay doing\nso alone?
I'll be fine. Watching you work so hard...\nIt made me want to do my part, too.
I understand. Please do, then.\nYou have my gratitude, Lathna!
Anything weird lately? Hm. I wanna say\nall the locals got together and prepared\nfor the festival like always...
Yeah, nothing really all that different from\nthe norm. We didn't have Banquo this year,\nthough, so everyone was a little quiet.
He was a popular guy around here. Mainly\nhelped get the lanterns done up every\nyear. He died a little while back, though.

That just naturally led to things being a
little more subdued. He always used to
be with his wife, too, but I didn't see her
either.
I see. Maybe she was too sad to leave\nthe house...
Hold your horses, now. I saw her.\nThat wife of his was out at the venue.
Yup. She happened to drop by while we\nwere gettin' ready. She fussed about with\nthe lanterns a bit. Was definitely her.
She did what?! Um... Which way did she\ngo? Do you know?
I do, 'cause when I went over to say hey,\nshe ran downriver! There nothin' down\nthere but a cave, though.
...! Thank you. I gotta go tell Cleo!
Hm, I see. So a woman who may have\ndone something to the lanterns fled to\na cave down the river.
This is quite the lead.\nSplendid work, sweetheart.
It's 'cause your secret plan worked so well,\nCleo.
Not at all. This time, it was all you.\nWithout your help, we wouldn't have\nsucceeded in this.

It...feels a little embarrassing to be
thanked for helping out like that, but
in a good way. I guess even I can be
helpful sometimes.
Of course you were! You were working\nhard to do something good because it's\nwhat YOU wanted to do.
Really? Even if ever since I was born, I've\nhad all this bad stuff going on with me?

Of course. The circumstances you were
born with and the things you choose to do
are different matters entirely. No matter
what happens, you are a good girl, Lathna.

Now then, I'm done preparing the next
round of meals, so let's leave things to our
friends in the refuge and head down the
river.
I want to get this situation resolved as\nsoon as possible, so that you and the\ntownsfolk can rest easy.
This is the cave that the lady talked about.
Looks like we were right to come here.\nLathna, stay behind me.
Have at you, foul aberrations!\nMy magic will expunge your rot!
